FALLEN boxing champ Scott Harrison is due to appear in court after cops swooped on his Glasgow home. Boxing champ Harrison due in court FALLEN boxing champ Scott Harrison is due to appear in court after cops swooped on his Glasgow home.The 37-year-old was arrested at his home in Mount Florida, on the south side of the city, by police acting on a European arrest warrant.He is understood to have spent the night in the cells and is due to appear at Edinburgh Sheriff Court later on Tuesday.Harrison now faces extradition to Spain in connection with an alleged assault.A Police Scotland spokeswoman said: &quot;A 37-year-old man was arrested by Police Scotland officers on a European arrest warrant.&quot; 